      • changeViewCB

        public ActionCallback changeViewCB(java.lang.String viewId,
                                   java.lang.String subId)
        Description copied from class: ProjectView
        Changes currently selected view and subview (if any).

        When default subview is requested:
        - if the view had never been selected then the first subview is selected
        - otherwise subview won't be changed

        It's an error when a view has no subviews and subId is not null.

        Specified by:
        changeViewCB in class ProjectView
        Parameters:
        viewId - id of view to be selected
        subId - id of subview to be selected
        Returns:
        callback which will be set to done if new content was selected or to rejected if content didn't change.

      • loadState

        public void loadState(Element parentNode)
        Description copied from interface: PersistentStateComponent
        This method is called when new component state is loaded. The method can and will be called several times, if config files were externally changed while IDE was running.

        State object should be used directly, defensive copying is not required.
